by WouterJ at 2015-08-25T20:07:52Z

The dump toolbar block showns the number of dumps on that page, which is nice. I think this should be done in the menu item as well.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by javiereguiluz at 2015-08-26T06:28:32Z

> The dump toolbar block showns the number of dumps on that page, which is nice. I think this should be done in the menu item as well.

That's correct. Why did we do this? In the old profiler, all panels are always enabled. In the new profiler, when some panel contains no information (for example when you dump nothing), that panel is disabled. So, if "dump" is disabled, don't click on it; if it's enabled, you can be certain that it contains dumped contents. In the new profiler, the badges of the menu are reserved to show the number of errors.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by javiereguiluz at 2015-08-26T06:32:42Z

> :-1: on changing the colors of the code block highlighting. These colors are the colors used for code examples throughout the Symfony docs (and after the exception page, throughout Symfony). We should keep that for consistency.

The colors are exactly the same ... we've only changed their shades. In this case, the consistency should not be achieved with the Symfony docs, but with the rest of the new Symfony profiler design. I prefer to maintain this change, merge it and let people test it before 2.8/3.0 release. If they think it's horrible, be sure they will loudly say so and we'll fix it.

